summaries.short: The final four tackle themed tablescapes before a team challenge that celebrates the LGBTQIA+ community with brilliant floral barges.
summaries.full: The final four are just a few stem snips away from the $100,000 grand prize as they tackle themed tablescapes and a team challenge that celebrates the LGBTQIA+ community with brilliant floral barges. While each designer has blown the judges away, only three can float into the finale.

summaries.short: The final florists create celebratory signature bouquets before transforming empty rooms into vibrant, flower-filled spaces that tell a story stunning enough to snag the life-changing $100,000 grand prize.
summaries.full: The final three florists face the threat of elimination as they create celebratory signature bouquets to be featured by a prominent national seller. Next, the top designers must transform empty rooms into vibrant, flower-filled spaces that tell a story stunning enough to snag the life-changing $100,000 grand prize.

summaries.short: Rose-centric chandeliers give each florist the chance to light up the competition before bold artistic visions see ordinary tree trunks turned into trees fit for a whimsical forest.
summaries.full: The fates of our florists are up in the air as they mount stunning, rose-centric chandelier displays. Next, bold artistic visions are put to the test with a team challenge that sees ordinary tree trunks transformed into trees fit for a whimsical floral forest.

summaries.short: After diving into a blind bouquet challenge, ten gifted florists split into squads to adorn life-sized chess sets with brilliant botanicals before members of the losing team create magic out of mystery for a chance to stay in the game.
summaries.full: After kicking off with a blind bouquet challenge, ten gifted florists split into groups to adorn life-sized chess sets with brilliant botanicals that tell a cohesive story through color balance and refined technique. Next, using mystery boxes designed by the judges as inspiration, members of the losing team hope their individual arrangements are stunning enough to keep them in the running for the $100,000 grand prize.

summaries.short: The six remaining florists transform bicycles and vintage cars into flower-powered masterpieces.
summaries.full: The six remaining florists shift gears, each designing a bicycle that embodies a fellow artist’s creative and personal essence before peeling off into teams to transform vintage cars into flower-powered masterpieces. Emotions run high as both groups fight to prove their worth.

summaries.full: See what's coming in Season 2 of Full Bloom.

summaries.short: The florists go from super-sized to super-small as they reimagine iconic Picasso portraits on an epic scale in hopes of dodging a miniature arrangement elimination round.
summaries.full: It's time to go big or go home as the artists reimagine iconic portraits on a gigantic scale. Tasked with “painting” larger-than-life canvasses, the teams carefully choose flowers that capture Picasso’s style and strokes, using texture to create dimension before switching gears for a miniature arrangement elimination round.

summaries.full: Relive highlights from episodes 03 and 04 of Full Bloom.

summaries.short: Two scrumptious challenges find the florists working with fresh fruits, veggies, and of course, flowers to create Baroque-inspired arrangements and larger-than-life cakes.
summaries.full: In the wake of a tough elimination, the florists are back and ready to prove their worth in a Baroque-inspired challenge incorporating a bounty of fresh fruits and vegetables. Next, the team leaders assume the role of head chef as the designers attempt to bake ten-foot cakes with flowers instead of flour.
